<p><b>Michael Duncan Buerk</b> (born 18 February 1946) is an English journalist and <a href="/wiki/News_presenter" title="News presenter">newsreader</a>, whose reporting of the <a href="/wiki/1984%E2%80%931985_famine_in_Ethiopia" class="mw-redirect" title="1984–1985 famine in Ethiopia">Ethiopian famine</a> on 23 October 1984 inspired the <a href="/wiki/Band_Aid_(band)" title="Band Aid (band)">Band Aid</a> charity record and, subsequently, the <a href="/wiki/Live_Aid" title="Live Aid">Live Aid</a> concert. Buerk has been the host of <a href="/wiki/BBC_Radio_4" title="BBC Radio 4">BBC Radio 4</a>'s <i><a href="/wiki/The_Moral_Maze" title="The Moral Maze">The Moral Maze</a></i> since 1990.</p>
<p></p>
