<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Trivia">Trivia</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Michael_Buerk&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Trivia">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Buerk was imitated by <a href="/wiki/Jon_Culshaw" title="Jon Culshaw">Jon Culshaw</a> on <i><a href="/wiki/Dead_Ringers_(comedy)" title="Dead Ringers (comedy)">Dead Ringers</a></i>.</p>
<p>Buerk's life and career has been the subject of a comedy musical, <i>Buerk! The Newsical</i> which debuted in London at the Network Theatre in May 2013.<sup id="cite_ref-29" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-29">[29]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-30" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-30">[30]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-31" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-31">[31]</a></sup></p>
